text:
Let’s Honor Lalibela’s Legacy Together

Selam Abel,

I deeply appreciate your work and the way your YouTube inspires and uplifts our community. Your dedication to faith and service to the Ethiopian Orthodox Church is truly admirable.

Lalibela is not just a historical site—it’s a sacred testimony of our faith, built by devotion and divine inspiration. But today, its preservation is at risk, relying heavily on unpredictable tourist donations. I believe we have a responsibility to ensure its legacy is honored and sustained for future generations.

With your voice and platform, we can spark a movement that strengthens Lalibela’s future while keeping its spiritual and historical significance alive. I’d love to hear your thoughts and explore ways we can contribute to this vision together.

May God bless your work always. Looking forward to connecting!

text:
Oriental Orthodox vs. Eastern Orthodox

The split happened in 451 AD at the Council of Chalcedon over Christ’s nature:

Oriental Orthodox (Non-Chalcedonian): Believe in Miaphysitism (one united divine-human nature).

Found in Ethiopia, Eritrea, Egypt (Coptic), Armenia, Syria, India.

Eastern Orthodox (Chalcedonian): Believe in Dyophysitism (two distinct natures, divine and human).

Found in Greece, Russia, Serbia, Bulgaria, Romania, Georgia, Ukraine, Turkey, Cyprus, etc.

The difference was mostly a theological misunderstanding, and modern dialogues show they have more in common than previously thought.
Thanks for the things you showed us keep it up. How many countries left to explore the whole world?
